{#
  hx-icon-button — Drupal Twig Template
  =======================================
  Icon-only action button with full accessibility support.
  Renders a square button (or anchor) containing a single icon.

  IMPORTANT: The `label` variable is REQUIRED for accessibility. It is
  rendered as both aria-label and title on the underlying element.
  The component renders nothing and emits a console warning when absent.

  IMPORTANT: The `hx-size` attribute (not `size`) controls button dimensions.
  This non-standard attribute name is required by the component API.

  Variables:
    - label     (string, required): Accessible name for the button. Required.
                Exposed as aria-label and title. Healthcare context: use a
                meaningful description like "Edit patient record" not "Edit".
    - variant   (string, optional): 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'tertiary' | 'danger' | 'ghost'.
                Default: 'ghost'.
    - hx_size   (string, optional): 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg'. Default: 'md'.
                Note: maps to the `hx-size` attribute (not `size`).
    - type      (string, optional): 'button' | 'submit' | 'reset'. Default: 'button'.
                Has no effect when href is set.
    - disabled  (bool, optional): Disables the button. Default: false.
    - href      (string, optional): When set, renders an <a> element instead of <button>.
    - name      (string, optional): Name for form submission (button mode only).
    - value     (string, optional): Value for form submission (button mode only).
    - icon      (markup, required): The icon markup to render in the default slot.
                Use hx-icon, an SVG element, or an <img>. Example:
                  <hx-icon name="edit" aria-hidden="true"></hx-icon>
    - attributes (object, optional): Additional Drupal attributes object.

  Usage:
    Icon button with hx-icon:
      {% include 'hx-icon-button.twig' with {
        label: 'Edit patient record',
        variant: 'ghost',
        hx_size: 'md',
        icon: '<hx-icon name="edit" aria-hidden="true"></hx-icon>',
      } %}

    Danger icon button (e.g., delete action):
      {% include 'hx-icon-button.twig' with {
        label: 'Delete appointment',
        variant: 'danger',
        icon: '<hx-icon name="trash" aria-hidden="true"></hx-icon>',
      } %}

    Link mode (renders as <a>):
      {% include 'hx-icon-button.twig' with {
        label: 'Download patient report',
        variant: 'secondary',
        href: node.field_report.url,
        icon: '<hx-icon name="download" aria-hidden="true"></hx-icon>',
      } %}

  Registration:
    Load the component script in your theme's .libraries.yml:
      hx-icon-button:
        js:
          path/to/@helixui/library/dist/hx-icon-button.js: { attributes: { type: module } }
#}

{% set _variant = variant|default('ghost') %}
{% set _size = hx_size|default('md') %}
{% set _type = type|default('button') %}

<hx-icon-button
  label="{{ label }}"
  variant="{{ _variant }}"
  hx-size="{{ _size }}"
  {% if not href %}type="{{ _type }}"{% endif %}
  {% if disabled %}disabled{% endif %}
  {% if href %}href="{{ href }}"{% endif %}
  {% if name %}name="{{ name }}"{% endif %}
  {% if value %}value="{{ value }}"{% endif %}
  {% if attributes %}{{ attributes }}{% endif %}
>
  {{ icon }}
</hx-icon-button>
